Experiment 5(d): Plan and Manage Tasks using Agile Tools (Trello, Jira)
Aim
To learn Agile principles and manage project development using Trello and Jira tools.
Theory
Agile methodology is an iterative approach that promotes flexibility, collaboration, and customer satisfaction.
Procedure / Steps
1.	Sign up for a free Trello account at https://trello.com.
2.	Create a new board named 'Full Stack Project'.
3.	Add lists: Backlog, To Do, In Progress, Code Review, Done.
4.	Add cards for each task and assign members and due dates.
5.	Sign up for Jira at https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira.
6.	Create a new project → Scrum template → Create backlog items and sprints.
7.	Track sprint progress using Burndown charts and Kanban boards.
Expected Output
Students should demonstrate a working Trello/Jira board with tasks moving from Backlog → Done.
Result
Successfully planned and managed project tasks using Agile tools.
